api.github.com/repos/gabime/spdlog/labels/wontfix","name":"wontfix","color":"a83a1c","default":true,"description":""},{"id":766135973,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw3NjYxMzU5NzM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gabime/spdlog/labels/workaround%20exists","name":"workaround exists","color":"fbca04","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2017-10-03T15:32:46Z","updated_at":"2019-06-19T16:14:12Z","closed_at":"2019-06-19T16:13:51Z","author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"```\r\nconst char* blah = \"I am a string\";\r\nSPDLOG_TRACE(logger, blah);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis fails to compile with the following errors:\r\n\r\n```\r\nmyfile.cpp: error: expected ‘)’ before ‘blah’\r\n         SPDLOG_TRACE(logger, blah);\r\n                              ^\r\nspdlog/spdlog.h:175:103: note: in definition of macro ‘SPDLOG_TRACE’\r\n   #define SPDLOG_TRACE(logger, ...) logger->trace(\"[ \" __FILE__ \":\" SPDLOG_STR_HELPER(__LINE__) \" ] \" __VA_ARGS__)\r\n                                                                                                       ^~~~~~~~~~~\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing the literal explicitly works fine:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSPDLOG_TRACE(logger, \"I am a string\");\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis compiles without complaint.\r\n\r\nUsing variables for arguments past the one representing `fmt` also does the job:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst char* blah = \"I am a string\";\r\nSPDLOG_TRACE(logger, \"format string {}\", blah);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis also compiles. It's only when a variable is used as the first argument (besides the logger).","closed_by":{"login":"gabime","id":6052198,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYwNTIxOTg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6052198?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.co